    "description":  "How to request a review and how to appeal to the Upper Tribunal.",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"what-otsi-must-tell-you\"\u003eWhat \u003cabbr title=\"Office of Trade Sanctions Implementation\"\u003eOTSI\u003c/abbr\u003e must tell you\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the Office of Trade Sanctions Implementation (\u003cabbr title=\"Office of Trade Sanctions Implementation\"\u003eOTSI\u003c/abbr\u003e), which is part of the Department for Business and Trade (\u003cabbr title=\"Department for Business and Trade\"\u003eDBT\u003c/abbr\u003e), has made a decision to impose a civil monetary penalty on you for a breach of trade sanctions (after they’ve informed you of their intention to do so and considered any representations you may have made), they must tell you: \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003ewhat their decision is \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003ethat you are entitled to seek a review \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003ethe date by which you must tell \u003cabbr title=\"Office of Trade Sanctions Implementation\"\u003eOTSI\u003c/abbr\u003e whether you want a review \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"requesting-a-review\"\u003eRequesting a review\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you request a review, the Secretary of State (or a delegated authority such as a minister or a senior official who is unconnected with the original decision) will review the monetary penalty.  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey may decide to: \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003euphold the decision to impose a penalty and its amount \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003euphold the decision to impose a penalty, but increase or lower the amount \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003ecancel the decision to impose a penalty \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"appealing-to-the-upper-tribunal\"\u003eAppealing to the Upper Tribunal \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou must seek a review before you can appeal to the Upper Tribunal.  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you’re unsatisfied with the decision, you may appeal to the Upper Tribunal. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you choose to appeal to the Upper Tribunal, it may: \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003euphold the decision to impose the penalty and its amount \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003euphold the decision to impose the penalty, but increase or lower the amount of the penalty  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003equash the decision to impose the penalty \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFind out \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/tax-upper-tribunal\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ehow to appeal to the Upper Tribunal\u003c/a\u003e. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"get-help\"\u003eGet help\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eContact \u003cabbr title=\"Office of Trade Sanctions Implementation\"\u003eOTSI\u003c/abbr\u003e using \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://submit.forms.service.gov.uk/form/3576/contact-otsi\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ethe enquiry form\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e",
